commit.message: Remove spaces in "check version update" target
Handle Mingw environment
Fix overflow on bad implementations of tanh()

AppVeyor: use Qt 6.5 in Qt6 Win64 build

Qt 6.3 has apparently been removed from the OS image.
Fix AppVeyor apt-get update in Ubuntu 20.04
Remove forward scattering peak from pseudo-reflection
Bump version to 0.3.1
Update "Using in Stellarium" documentation

Don't embed Rayleigh phase function in the example's texture

When it's embedded, the resulting texture becomes badly conditioned for
interpolation. In particular, there appears a strange "cap" around the
zenith, where the interpolant is overly curved by bilinear filtering.

Computing the phase function on the fly, as will be the effect of this
commit, changes fullscreen ShowMySky performance on my Intel UHD
Graphics 620 from about 26 FPS to about 25.5 FPS, which corresponds to a
frame rate limit of 1326 FPS if this were the only thing computed.

Make sure OpenGL command stream is flushed before starting timing

It's already being done after drawing commands, but apparenly, Qt's
internals do something with a variable complexity before calling
QOpenGLWidget::paintGL(), which influences GPU load inconsistently
from frame to frame, so we need to *start* timing from a flushed
command stream state too.

Add a workaround for poor NPOT mipmap implementations

We use the deepest mipmap level as the average of texture data in order
to compute integrals in EclipsedDoubleScatteringPrecomputer. Some OpenGL
implementations, however, appear to handle non-power-of-two textures
poorly when computing mipmap levels. The result is that, when a texture
dimension is close to a power of two but not exactly it, the whole mip
map displays ugly aliasing, and the deepest 1×1 level is very far from
the average of the texels of level 0.

To work around such OpenGL implementations, we resize the base level
texture to the closest smaller power-of-two texture, and compute the mip
map from it instead of the initial texture. The resize introduces a
small inaccuracy, but the result is still much higher quality than if we
used glGenerateMipmap() on the initial NPOT texture.

On good implementations such as NVIDIA GPU drivers, the workaround is
disabled.

Fixes #14

Fix a special case in sRGB transfer function

When c==0.0031308, the function used to have both branches of the
piecewise computation evaluate to true, which led to a value twice as
much as the expected one.
Bump version to 0.3.0
Do finish saving the texture when NaN is detected, for diagnostics

Add a check for non-monotonic cos() in GLSL

A Chebyshoff polynomial fit will be used for sin() and cos() in
ShowMySky previewer if non-monotonicity of the built-in GLSL
cos() is detected.

Fix installation path of CMake config modules
